# Harness engineering (`src/test/harness`)

## Purpose

Harnesses make agent-heavy domains **fast, deterministic, and inspectable**: no WASM startup, no real media I/O unless an explicit integration test says otherwise.

## When to add a harness

- Any new **non-trivial pure utility** (correlation math, command building, layout math) should get:
  - A small module under `src/test/harness/` (or `legibility/` for snapshot/audit helpers), and
  - Vitest coverage colocated or in [src/test/harness/harness.test.ts](src/test/harness/harness.test.ts).

## Patterns in this repo

- **Synthetic data**: e.g. [syncHarness.ts](src/test/harness/syncHarness.ts) — typed fake signals / validators without large buffers.
- **FFmpeg mock**: [ffmpegHarness.ts](src/test/harness/ffmpegHarness.ts) — virtual FS, checks `-i` inputs exist, returns canned outputs.
- **Legibility**:
  - [CanvasSnapshot.ts](src/test/harness/legibility/CanvasSnapshot.ts) — serialize Konva `Stage` structure for tests or debugging.
  - [FFmpegAudit.ts](src/test/harness/legibility/FFmpegAudit.ts) — append-only audit log of commands/args.

## Commands

- Run **`npm run test:harness`** (`vitest run --dir src/test/harness`) before relying on harness-only changes; it should stay green and fast.

## Production bundles

- Legibility imports are for **tests, dev-only hooks, or diagnostics** — avoid bloating production bundles with debug-only Konva/audit paths unless behind explicit dev gates.
